 JOB DETAILS 
 
 Department:  Business Intelligence and Insights 
 
 Job Title:  Business Intelligence and Insights Specialist 
 
 Reports To (title):  Business Intelligence and Insights Manager 
 
 Career Level:  3 
 
 Location:  HOME/REMOTE 
 
 Line Management Responsibility:  No 
 
 ** Please note we ask that your work day includes times from 12p and 3p UTC to run in congruence with this global team** 
 Job Purpose: 
 You are joining an early-stage business intelligence team who function as an independent unit responsible for the end-to-end design of analytics reporting suites for internal customers across the business. Named the business‚Äô ‚ÄúMost Innovative Team‚Äù in 2020, the Business Intelligence and Insights group works primarily within the Microsoft Power Platform to develop and maintain reports that serve audiences from front-line data collectors to the executive committee. 
 WHAT‚ÄôS YOUR NEW ROLE ABOUT? 
 
 In your role as a Business Intelligence & Insights Specialist, you will manage a portfolio of internal clients from intake through production to ensure that they receive reporting that provides operational efficiency, transparency, and actionable insights. You can expect to be actively building projects for 1-2 new clients at any particular time. 
 Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets and communicate analysis and findings in a clear and concise manner
 Build, test, deliver & support reporting analytics utilizing Power BI visualisations where possible 
 Develop and maintain strong relationships with internal stakeholders through the delivery of consistent & supportable analytical solutions
 Provide support and assistance toward the design and architecture of a maturing Power BI environment, including designing and managing the associated dataset architecture 
 Partner with cross functional teams to define and develop robust data models from complex data sets
 Train and onboard users of varying data literacy levels, including data discovery, report creation, and ongoing usage 
 Work with established business systems and processes, third party products, and data sources as required 
 DO YOU HAVE THESE ESSENTIALS? 
 
 2+ years of experience in analytics, business intelligence, or visualizations/dashboarding
 Demonstrable full-stack expertise with the Power BI platform & supporting technologies, including aesthetically pleasing and user-friendly front-end development and UX/UI design 
 Ability to create a clear narrative from data via reports, presentations, and communication
 Data warehouse design and development using multi-dimensional modeling techniques
 Intermediate to expert T-SQL skills including creating stored procedures, views, and indexes as well as performance tuning queries
 Professional curiosity about the field, including familiarity with top resources and emerging innovations in analytics reporting 
 IT WOULD BE GREAT IF YOU HAD THESE DESIRABLES TOO 
 Experience working on an Agile development team
 High degree of comfort with the Atlassian suite, specifically Jira and Confluence 
 Experience with enterprise deployment of a business intelligence tool
 Hands-on statistical programing language experience (i.e. R and/or Python) 
 Familiarity with other business intelligence dashboarding software (Tableau, SAP BusinessObjects, Spotfire, Domo, etc.) 
 
